cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CC

This paper deals with the logical foundations of short-circuit evaluation, a concept that is widely used in programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages), followed by cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses different variants of short-circuit logic, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
